Happy Valentine’s Day my loves🤍

#StoryTimeWithNitibha 
Relationships have always been a BIG part of who I am, but surprisingly enough, I've never spoken about them on my social media, where I share every little aspect of my life. Maybe because I always thought this should be kept private or maybe because I never felt confident enough to put my love life out there for the world to see. Needless to say, I am still figuring it out, there's a lot going on in the background as we speak, my love life has some how never been smooth or simple- its come with its share of complications. These relationships might not have had the happy ending every girl dreams of, but they've taught me some of the most valuable lessons & have led me to create some amazing bonds that I will cherish for life & for that- I will always be grateful. 

So this one's for all the single ladies, I know days like Valentine's can be a tough reminder on how you still haven't found THE one, but its also days like these that should remind you to love yourself first, to prioritise YOU over anyone else & to celebrate life no matter what your relationship status might be. Don’t be afraid to love again, to make mistakes, to stumble, to fall, until you get what you deserve, and that is nothing but the best ❤️

latestPosts.caption:
Took two days off work to celebrate something I’ve rarely spoken about — my Kashmiri roots 🧡

My cousin’s Mekhal (Yagnopavit) ceremony — a deeply sacred tradition in the Kashmiri Pandit community — brought our entire family together in the most beautiful way. Unlike big, loud celebrations, this one was calm… intentional… filled with meaning.

I don’t always show this side of me — but it’s a big part of who I am. And it felt right to let you in on it 💫

Wearing @rajiramniq 
Jewellery @shilpigoyaljewellery
